                                                                               "details":  {
                                                                                               "body":  "\u003cp\u003eThe SSRO Director of Investigations is responsible for:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eProduction of relevant statutory guidance, reports templates and user guides, developing SSRO guidance to respond to new issues and to find ways to improve value for money for the taxpayer while ensuring a fair return for industry\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eConducting investigations, in response to referrals, so that the SSRO efficiently dispatches its duty to provide independent expert advice on single source contracts\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eOverseeing the reporting and compliance of industry and the Ministry of Defence with the Regulations, including the requirement to report profit and Allowable Costs on qualifying defence contracts, ensuring that all data provided is consistent with SSRO policy and requirements\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eDeveloping the investigative function of the organisation, so that it becomes a trusted and function that is used by government and industry\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n",
